This paper deals with the optimal deployment of unmanned aerial vehicles (UAVs) as communication relays, which involves the use of information theory, networking, control systems, robotics, and optimization. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the mathematical foundations of information and communication. The paper also involves the study of communication networks, which falls under the sub-category cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The use of UAVs as relays also involves control systems and robotics, which are covered by the sub-category cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also discusses the optimization of UAV locations, which falls under the sub-category cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper uses tools from quantization theory, which is covered by the sub-category cs.MA (Machine Learning).
